d:["$","section",null,{"id":"why","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"section-label","children":"03 // Capabilities"}],["$","h2",null,{"children":["The moat is what",["$","br",null,{}],"accumulates."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"feature-grid","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"feature-card","style":"$undefined","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"01"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"Override Corpus"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["Every time your team overrides Mergen's recommendation, that decision is encoded as policy. After six months of production: your Friday settlement windows, your compliance holds, your on-call's preferred fixes — ",["$","span",null,{"className":"highlight","children":"structured, queryable, and impossible to replicate from a standing start."}]," The diagnosis algorithm is reproducible. The accumulated operational memory of your infrastructure is not."]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"feature-card","style":{"gridColumn":"8 / span 5","marginTop":"5rem"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"02"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"Agent Blunder Log"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["Every autonomous action Mergen's safety layer blocks is recorded with its reason: allowlist block, RBAC rejection, override corpus halt, planning gate denial.",["$","span",null,{"className":"highlight","children":" The headline number is \"prevented\" — autonomous actions your on-call didn't have to handle."}]," ","This is the answer to \"why would you trust an AI agent with prod?\" The system blocked itself, logged why, and waited."]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"feature-card","style":{"gridColumn":"2 / span 5"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"03"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"Autonomous Incident Loop"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["PagerDuty fires → causal analysis across all telemetry → override corpus consulted → fix executes at ",["$","span",null,{"className":"highlight","children":"≥85% confidence"}]," → validated (error count before/after) → RESOLVED posted to your Slack thread. Engineer wakes up to a closed incident and a full audit trail. MTTR: 5 minutes. Manual: 45."]}]]}],["$","div","04",{"className":"feature-card","style":{"gridColumn":"8 / span 4","marginTop":"-1rem"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"04"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"Institutional Memory"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["Every resolved incident generates a structured postmortem, indexed by"," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"highlight","children":"BM25 + TF-IDF hybrid retrieval"}],". When an agent opens a file, the IDE receives relevant past incidents automatically — before it's asked, before it writes a line. Future agents don't re-discover constraints that burned your on-call at 3am six months ago."]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"feature-card","style":"$undefined","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"05"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"5-Minute MTTR"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["Designed for the ",["$","span",null,{"className":"highlight","children":"sleep-deprived on-call engineer"}],". Mergen resolves routine production incidents in under 5 minutes — replacing 45 minutes of manual dashboard jumping, log grepping, and Slack back-and-forth. The impact report shows autonomous MTTR vs. manual MTTR, per failure mode, as a shareable PDF your CTO can present to the board."]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"feature-card","style":"$undefined","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"feature-num","children":"06"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"feature-title","children":"Local-First. VPC-Ready."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"feature-desc","children":["Mergen runs ","$L15",". No Datadog required to start — point it at Docker containers or drop one import into your Node.js entry point. PII shield is always on. Execution audit trail written to ","$L16"," as immutable JSONL. Cloud mode adds TLS, SSO, RBAC, and per-tenant event isolation when you need it."]}]]}]]}]]}]
